Description: Open-source desktop database client and management tool
 Tablio is a free, open-source desktop database client built with Rust
 and React. It provides a modern native interface for connecting to
 PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaDB, SQLite, CockroachDB, and TiDB databases
 from one application.
 .
 Features include a high-performance data grid with inline editing,
 SQL query console with syntax highlighting, visual query execution
 plan viewer, JSON column editor, pg_stat performance insights,
 schema management, and data import/export.
